South Korea Equity Movers: Korea Zinc, OCI Co., Poongsan

-- B y   S a e r o m i   S h i n
-- 
2011-09-29T00:52:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-29/south-korea-equity-movers-korea-zinc-oci-co-poongsan.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in  South Korea  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 9:42 a.m. in Seoul.  The  Kospi Index (KOSPI)  lost 0.4 percent to 1,715.48, falling for a
second day. The gauge has lost 18 percent since June 30, its
worst quarterly performance since the last three months of 2008.  Metals-related companies: Poongsan Corp. (103140 KS), a
copper-products maker, slipped 5.4 percent to 24,500 won. Korea
Zinc Co. (010130 KS), which produces gold and silver, retreated
8.5 percent to 280,500 won. Gold for immediate delivery fell for
a second day, dropping as much as 1.6 percent. Copper for
delivery in three months on the London Metal Exchange fell 5.9
percent.  OCI Co. (010060 KS), South Koreaâ€™s biggest maker of
polysilicon, rose 2.1 percent to 19,850 won. The company plans
to buy back 400,000 shares in the next three months starting
today, according to a regulatory filing. It will cancel the
shares as soon as they are purchased.  To contact the reporter on this story:
